:INFO
The Novel That Is Exactly as Long as It Needs to Be
Piranesi is 272 pages and every one of them is necessary. Susanna Clarke's \
second novel is about a man named Piranesi who lives in a vast labyrinthine \
house full of statues and halls and tides, and who keeps meticulous journals \
about his world. The mystery of who he is and how he got there unfolds with \
extraordinary precision. I read it in one afternoon and then sat quietly for \
a while because the feeling it left was not like any other novel I had finished.

:NOTE.half
Do not read anything about this before you start. Just start.
|
